					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">freem wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">According to <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Standard_controller" class="postlink">the wiki</a>, Paperboy does. Other games might; I'm not sure.</div><br />It says: &quot;Paperboy relies on this behavior and requires that reads from the controller ports return exactly $40 or $41 as appropriate.&quot; It seems to me, this means it only cares when actually reading like <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">LDA $4016</tt>, so it isn't the complete use of the open bus.<br /><br />However, if writing an emulator you should emulate the full behavior of the open bus, even if nothing known currently uses it. Doing so would improve the accuracy, and may also be useful in future.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="gopher://zzo38computer.org/" class="postlink">.</a></div>
